Drop the real inbound RFP PDF in this directory, renamed to `rfp-inbound.pdf`.

Then from your terminal (not inside Claude), run:

    costate upload rfp-inbound.pdf

The CLI uses Microsoft's `markitdown` under the hood to convert PDF / DOCX /
PPTX / XLSX / images / audio and writes the result to your workspace as
`rfp-inbound.md`. Your drafter agents can then search it, cite sections,
and split it into tasks.

Prereq: `pipx install 'markitdown[all]'` (one-time install).

This placeholder file can be deleted once the real RFP is in the workspace.
